      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N0_INTRO_A",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A riveted label plate sits beside the pneumatic tube intake. (pause) Scratched clean from hands checking it after the shack went quiet.",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "key": "knowledge.tubeRoutesNoted",
              "op": "==",
              "value": false
            }
          ],
          "next": "N1_INTRO_B"
        },
        {
          "id": "N1_INTRO_B",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Black enamel text, arrows, and department names. The plate looks more maintained than the door.",
          "next": "N2_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N2_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK",
              "text": "look \u2014 Read the plate.",
              "next": "N3_LOOK_A"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE",
              "text": "use \u2014 Record routing in notes.",
              "next": "N6_LOG_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK",
              "text": "ask \u2014 What does this imply?",
              "next": "N4_ASK_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_TALK",
              "text": "talk \u2014 Try the call box about tube routes.",
              "next": "N5_TALK_A"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SHOW",
              "text": "show \u2014 Show OLEA credentials; request official routing diagram.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "flag",
                  "key": "auth.oleaOnSiteToken",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N10_SHOW_PASS_A",
              "onFailNext": "N11_SHOW_FAIL_A"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave \u2014 Back.",
              "next": "N20_LEAVE_A"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N3_LOOK_A",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The arrows form a clean loop, like someone wanted the order to be undeniable.",
          "next": "N3_LOOK_B"
        },
        {
          "id": "N3_LOOK_B",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "\u201cRECORDS \u2194 SECURITY \u2194 OPERATIONS\u201d (labeled even if dead)",
          "next": "N2_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N4_ASK_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Why list routes on a dead system?",
          "next": "N4_ASK_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N4_ASK_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The plate doesn\u2019t answer. It does what signage does here: insists someone once needed this true.",
          "next": "N2_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N5_TALK_A",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The call box speaker crackles as if it\u2019s been waiting to be blamed.",
          "next": "N5_TALK_B"
        },
        {
          "id": "N5_TALK_B",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CALL_BOX",
          "text": "\u201cRouting information is not operational guidance. For operational guidance, contact Security. For Security, contact Operations. For Operations\u2014\u201d",
          "next": "N5_TALK_C"
        },
        {
          "id": "N5_TALK_C",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CALL_BOX",
          "text": "\u201c\u2014contact Records.\u201d",
          "next": "N5_TALK_D"
        },
        {
          "id": "N5_TALK_D",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CALL_BOX",
          "text": "\u201cThis loop is for accountability, not speed. That\u2019s not an admission. It\u2019s terminology.\u201d",
          "next": "N5_TALK_E"
        },
        {
          "id": "N5_TALK_E",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "So the tubes connect them.",
          "next": "N5_TALK_F"
        },
        {
          "id": "N5_TALK_F",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CALL_BOX",
          "text": "\u201cConnect is informal.\u201d",
          "next": "N5_TALK_G"
        },
        {
          "id": "N5_TALK_G",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CALL_BOX",
          "text": "\u201cThey are related via labeled conveyance pathways. Related does not mean available.\u201d",
          "next": "N2_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N10_SHOW_PASS_A",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The call box has a slot for credentials. (pause) It\u2019s taped over with a strip reading: \u201cTEMPORARY \u2014 DO NOT MAKE PERMANENT.\u201d",
          "next": "N10_SHOW_PASS_B"
        },
        {
          "id": "N10_SHOW_PASS_B",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Even if you had the token, access is still a story someone has to agree to.",
          "next": "N2_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N11_SHOW_FAIL_A",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The call box has a credentials slot. (pause) It\u2019s taped over with a strip: \u201cTEMPORARY \u2014 DO NOT MAKE PERMANENT.\u201d",
          "next": "N11_SHOW_FAIL_B"
        },
        {
          "id": "N11_SHOW_FAIL_B",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Requires: on-site authorization token / active Security presence.",
          "next": "N2_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N6_LOG_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Log it.",
          "next": "N7_LOG_NARR_A"
        },
        {
          "id": "N7_LOG_NARR_A",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You copy the routing exactly. Your pen hesitates on \u201cSECURITY\u201d like it might object.",
          "next": "N8_LOG_NARR_B"
        },
        {
          "id": "N8_LOG_NARR_B",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The plate\u2019s relationship goes into your paperwork as a procedural note, not a theory.",
          "next": "N9_END_OUTCOME_NOTE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N9_END_OUTCOME_NOTE",
          "type": "end",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Tube routing plate: RECORDS \u2194 SECURITY \u2194 OPERATIONS (labeled even if dead).",
          "outcomeId": "note_tube_routes",
